{{DISPLAYTITLE:''Dictionnaire de la langue française'' (''Littré'')}}
[[File:Littré - 1863 - A-C - page de titre.jpg|thumb]]
The '''''Dictionnaire de la langue française''''' by [[Émile Littré]], commonly called simply the "'''''Littré'''''", is a four-volume [[dictionary]] of the [[French language]] published in Paris by Hachette.<ref>http://littre.reverso.net/dictionnaire-francais/</ref>

The dictionary was originally issued in 30 parts, 1863–72; a second edition is dated 1872–77.<ref>http://www.littre.org</ref><ref>''[[OED]]''</ref>  A further edition is reported in 1877, published by [[Hachette Livre|Hachette]].

An on-line version is available for PC, Mac and IOS (app for iPhone, iPad and iPod):  [http://www.littre.org].

The [[British Library]]'s on-line integrated catalogue describes the contents as: ''1o Pour la nomenclature''...: ''2o Pour la grammaire''...: 3o ''Pour la signification des mots''...: 4o ''Pour la partie historique''...: 5o ''Pour l’étymologie''..

