{{italic title}} [[File:Ensiklopedi Adinegoro.jpg|thumb|right|Cover]] '''''Ensiklopedi umum dalam bahasa Indonesia''''' (''{{lang-en|General encyclopedia in Indonesian language}}'') is a single volume [[Indonesian language]] [[general encyclopedia]] published in 1954 by [[Bulan Bintang]].<ref>{{cite encyclopedia | encyclopedia = Ensiklopedi Umum | title = Adinegoro | author = Hassan Shadily | author-link = Hassan Shadily | author2 = Ag. Pringgodigdo| author2-link = Ag. Pringgodigdo | publisher = Kanisius | isbn = 9794135224 | year = 1973 | page = 281 }}</ref><ref>{{cite book | title = Perpustakaan Sekolah | author = Darmono | publisher = Grasindo | isbn = 9797599396 | page = 180 | year = }}</ref><ref>{{cite book | title = Verguisd en vergeten: Tan Malaka, de linkse beweging en de Indonesische revolutie, 1945-1949 | volume = 3 | author = Harry A. Poeze | publisher = [[KITLV Uitgeverij]] | year = 2008 | page = 2042 | isbn = 9067182583 }}</ref> It was written solely by [[Adi Negoro]].<ref>{{cite book | title = Leksikon Susastra Indonesia | author = Korrie Layun Rampan | author-link = Korrie Layun Rampan | publisher = PT Balai Pustaka | year = 2001 | pages = 16–17 | isbn = 9796663589 }}</ref> It is claimed to be the second Indonesian encyclopedia that was the work of a single person.<ref>From the book's foreword: [[s:id:Ensiklopedi Umum Dalam Bahasa Indonesia]]</ref>
It consists of 404 pages and contains around 2,200 entries.<ref>{{cite book | title = Katalog beranotasi: ensiklopedia, kamus, dan daftar istilah bahasa Indonesia, 1741-1995 | author = Jérôme Samuel | author2 = Meity Taqdir Qodratillah | publisher = Yayasan Obor Indonesia | year = 2001 | page = 3 | isbn = 979685127X }}</ref>
After that, in 1955 ''[[Ensiklopedia Indonesia]]'' by [[Todung Sunan Gunung Mulia]] was published by publisher [[W. van Hoeve]], Bandung (not to be confused by 1980's ''[[Ensiklopedi Indonesia]]'' published by [[Ichtiar Baru van Hoeve]], Jakarta).<ref>http://maulanusantara.wordpress.com/2010/06/07/mengenang-putra-sang-fajar-6-juni-1901-6-juni-2010/</ref><ref>http://www.ibvh.com/web2/ei/</ref>
